<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Kalmia</i> <i>microphylla</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the dwarf shrub canopy and herbaceous layer with shrubs <i>Phyllodoce</i> <i>breweri</i>, <i>Phyllodoce</i> <i>empetriformis</i>, <i>Rhododendron</i> <i>columbianum</i> and <i>Vaccinium</i> <i>cespitosum</i> and herbs:<i>Allium</i> <i>validum</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>aquatilis</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>nigricans</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>scopulorum</i>, <i>Deschampsia</i> <i>cespitosa</i>, <i>Pedicularis</i> <i>groenlandica</i>, <i>Phleum</i> <i>alpinum</i> or <i>Symphyotrichum</i> <i>spathulatum</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Pinus</i> <i>contorta</i> ssp. <i>murrayana</i> and <i>Pinus</i> <i>monticola</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 50 cm; canopy is intermittent to continuous. Herbaceous layer is herb-rich. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Subalpine to alpine wet meadows, nutrient-poor fens, snow beds, lake margins, low-gradient depressions. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Kalmia microphylla</i> and <i>K. polifolia</i> as a OBL plants. </div>
</div>

		
